The paper discusses the development of agents that perform well against humans in imperfect information games, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of historical behavioral data to generate a predictive model also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve human subjects playing a game, indicating a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of simulations and uncertainty reduction suggests a focus on stochastic systems (cs.SI).
